The Economic and Financial Crime Commission (EFCC) Kaduna Zonal office said it has recovered monies in naira and foreign currencies and several forfeited properties running into billions of naira within the past one year. This was disclosed by the zonal head, Mr. Mailafia Yakubu at a press conference while giving a rundown of activities under his leadership at the zone within the period under review. According to him, a total of 871 (eight hundred and seventy one) petitions were received, with about 159 (one hundred and fifty nine) cases with the Legal and Prosecution Directorate for legal advice, while a total of 126 (one hundred and twenty six) petitions were rejected and transferred to various collaborating agencies as they do not fall under the purview of the EFCC’s mandate”. “A whooping total of 30 (thirty) convictions were recorded in the time under review. Furthermore, the results of rigorous investigations carried out by the zone shows the following recoveries between June 2019 to date as a total N717,618,281.755 (seven hundred and seventeen million, six hundred and eighteen thousand, two hundred and eighty one Naira, seventy five kobo) and $206,798.00 (two hundred and six thousand, seven hundred and ninety eight US dollars).